Ground Systems (UGS) and specialized payloads that empower SOF Operators with unparalleled intelligence, surveillance, and
reconnaissance capabilities that meet the unique demands of SOF missions across multiples domains in the most challenging
environments. sUMS development focuses on a reduction in the operator cognitive workload through an integrated suite of
stealthy, autonomous and AI enabled systems that penetrate and persist in denied environments, provide continuous over-watch,
rapidly pinpoint and prosecute time-sensitive targets, and over-match adversaries - making SOF teams ubiquitous, undetectable,
and unbeatable on the modern battlefield.

FY 2026 Plans:
FY 2026 Plans: Continue development, test, evaluation, and integration of emerging technologies into multi-domain sUMS
platforms including increasing on-board edge computing power and data storage, multi-domain secure communications between
robots, and multi-mission payload prototyping for user evaluation and future production. Conduct developmental and operational
testing and evaluation of ultra-light, untethered, micro, medium range/medium endurance, and containerized sUAS.
FY 2027 Plans:
FY 2027 Plans: Continues advancing sUMS platforms through continuous development, testing, and integration of emerging
technologies to address the need for unmanned and advanced multi-domain systems that enhance SOF capabilities in
denied environments. Efforts include the continued integration of on-board edge computing power to support the integration of
autonomous UAS capabilities and secure communication between UGS. Development will be initiated for a common UAS ground
control station to reduce operator workload, a specialized UAS to support multi-mission sensor and communication payloads, and
man-packable & team-transportable UGS.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Increase of $20.944 supports the development of a common UAS ground control station to reduce operator workload, a
specialized UAS to support multi-mission sensor and communication payloads, and man-packable & team-transportable UGS.
It enables a comprehensive portfolio of systems ranging from low-cost, mission-specific platforms to highly advanced capable
technologies.
