BCN. Update BOA space sensor to support regional threat and raid tracking. Update Enterprise Sensor Processing Node (ESPN)
to provide cruise missile indications and warning. Plan, design, and integrate the communication infrastructure for Guam Defense
System sites including Increment 1 and 2 command nodes, sensors, and launchers. Initiate and establish secure and resilient
networks/communications connections for the Defense of Guam. Upgrade C2BMC and BOA to include support of a C2BMC Node
on Island and BOA development for theater threat space. This project supports the Department's Pacific Deterrence Initiative
(PDI), USINDOPACOM Guam Defense System requirements, and Guam Defense System Joint Program Office Increment 1 and
2 Deliveries. The Missile Defense System on Guam will form a key part of strategic deterrence, is a critical component of U.S.
Integrated Air and Missile Defense strategy, and supports the Department's PDI investments in the Indo-Pacific region.

- Continue enhancement of ESPN capabilities for cruise missile indication and warning.
- Continue Guam Command Center deployment development and hardware procurement.
- Establish secure and resilient networks/communications connections for the Guam Defense System Increment 1 Early
Operational and Increment 2 Initial Operational Capabilities.
- Continue BOA development for incorporating emergent INDOPACOM regional threats.
- Continue C2BMC development, integration and testing for Guam Defense System Initial Operational Capability.

Specific and/or unique accomplishments for each FY are as follows:

FY 2026 Plans:
- SEE ABOVE.
FY 2027 Plans:
- Installation of the resilient network communications infrastructure for the Guam Defense System Early Operational Capability,
including secure fiber optic and Defense Red Switch Network connectivity to Missile Defense System sites.
- Develop and purchase Knowledge Wall equipment for integration into the Guam Command Center.
- Develop and purchase C2BMC Mission Node equipment, including but not limited to rack hardware for the Mission Suite,
Mission Node Gateway, Guam Management Node, and External User Support Suite and Gateway.
