Title: Missile Defense System - Next: JTIFC Upgrades                                                                                       0.000       0.000          47.000
                                                                                                                            Articles:         -           -               -
Description: This effort accelerates the delivery of Joint Tactical Integrated Fire Control (JTIFC) architecture capabilities
in support of the Missile Defense System-Next capabilities and adds direct support to the integration of JTIFC into Missile
Defense System as well as the Limited Area Defense (LAD) sites. This includes distributed combat identification (d-JMAC), joint
automated battle management engagement coordination (EC) and electronic protection (EP) through the Joint Track Management
Capability Bridge (JTMC) Bridge to enable integrated C2 across Service weapon systems and sub-systems. JTIFC upgrades
will provide performance improvements over any single system through a system of systems approach to seamless integration.
Specifically, integrating multi-domain combat identification capabilities, joint automated management / engagement coordination
improves integrated defensive fires and reduces effector wastage.

Service program of records are dependent on accelerated JTIFC core capabilities and software (JTMC Bridge, d-JMAC, Joint
Automated Battle Management Aides (ABMA)/EC, and EP) for the LAD architecture and MDA plays a critical role in JTIFC
integration, engineering and fielding of JTIFC capabilities into the Missile Defense System-Next architecture, including the Missile
Defense System and LAD architectures (e.g., fielding of D-JMAC software increases Warfighter's decision space). Additionally,
there are increased requirements for JTIFC Architecture and JTMC Bridge capabilities in Service and Combatant Command
demonstrations/exercises and in regional theaters. Finally, a digital and hardware infrastructure is necessary to rapidly prototype,
integrate and test JTFIC integration with the Missile Defense System and LADs.

Efforts include:
- Missile Defense System-Next specific cross-Service systems engineering, requirements definition, and interface control to
integrate the JTIFC architecture, including the JTMC-B, into the Missile Defense System-Next architecture.
- Definition of candidate Missile Defense System-Next LAD capability phasing increments and C2 requirements.
- Operationalize and field the JTMC Bridge capability within Service Programs of Record (systems or sub-systems) to include:
Army's Integrated Battle Command System, Navy's Aegis Weapon System and Cooperative Engagement Capability, Air Force's
Tactical Operations Center - Light and Air Based Air Defense System, and Marine Corps' Composite Tracking Node.
- Development and demonstration of JTIFC capabilities within Missile Defense System-Next architectures using Live, Virtual and
Constructive hardware in the loop environments.

