A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The Small Business Innovation Research (SBIR) and the Small Business Technology Transfer (STTR) programs provide the means for stimulating technological
innovation in the private sector, strengthens the role of small business in meeting the Department of Defense (DoD) research and development needs; fosters and
encourages participation of minority and disadvantaged businesses in technological innovation; and increases the commercial application of the DoD supported
research and development results. These efforts are responsive to Public Law 106-554 and the SBIR and STTR Extension Act of 2022 (Public Law 117-183).

