D. Acquisition Strategy
USSF is developing the Protected Anti-Jam Tactical System (PATS) in an evolutionary manner to introduce Protected Tactical Waveform (PTW) capabilities providing
anti-jam (AJ) communications via military and commercial satellite systems for tactical users in all Services, initially providing service over the existing military Wideband
Global SATCOM (WGS) system and then adding commercial and purpose-built Protected Tactical SATCOM satellites. The PTES Program was designated initially
as a Rapid Prototyping effort in June 2018 from the NDAA for Fiscal Year 2016 (Public Law 114-92) under Middle Tier of Acquisitions (MTA) for Rapid Prototyping/
Rapid Fielding (Section 804) to kick off the design, development, integration and testing with PTW service via WGS. The PTES program competitively awarded a single
Cost-Plus Incentive Fee (CPIF) contract to Boeing on 26 November 2018 to develop and field the PTES, through declaration of FOC planned for FY 2026. Boeing and
subcontractors developed all PTES segments and performed / will perform all system integration, including end-to-end tests of the complete PTES system. Raytheon is
the major sub-contractor to develop the End Cryptographic Units. The program office will secure Cloud and Infrastructure services from approved and secure sources.
Tobyhanna Army Depot will be responsible for key loading and initialization of PTW-capable modems. The 45th Test Squadron (PTES Developmental Test), STAR Delta
12 / 4th Test and Evaluation Squadron (PTES Operational Test), Joint Support and Enabling Command, and Joint Interoperability Test Command support test events.
On 31 May 2023, the PTES Program Office transitioned the program from a Middle Tier Acquisition (MTA) into the Execution Phase of the Software Acquisition Pathway
upon a successful Operational Demonstration of PTW over Wideband Global SATCOM and satisfying the corresponding MTA requirements.




