Conduct quick-reaction troubleshooting and deficiency resolution for ECU during on-orbit demonstration and test activities.
Continue planning and acquiring PTS-R's ECUs, to include initiating NSA certification processes.
FY 2025 to FY 2026 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY 2026 decreased due to completion of PTS-P ECU development and NSA certification.
Title: PTS-P/R Ground Development                                                                                                        10.537       3.819         0.000
Description: Develops and incorporates Mission Management System and Key Management System (MMS/KMS) modifications
of the Protected Tactical Enterprise Service (PTES) program ground capability to plan and manage PTS, the associated
cryptographic material and the SATCOM links they enable. Also develops and incorporates modifications to MMS of the WGS
program ground capability (i.e. Common Network Planning Software (CNPS) and Wideband SATCOM Trend Analysis and
Anomaly Resolution System (WSTARS).

FY 2025 Plans:
Continue analysis of the WGS CNPS planning system, which provides the overarching management of all sub-systems, providing
situational awareness to all users of the Wideband SATCOM Operational Management System.
FY 2026 Plans:
N/A
FY 2025 to FY 2026 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY 2026 decreased due to delay of PTES integration requirements and deferring MMS capability upgrades for PTS P/R efforts.
Title: PTS-P Gateway Development                                                                                                          6.196       7.816         3.433
Description: Develop the Gateway Segment, also called PTS Ground Entry Terminal-Prototype (PGET-P), for integration with
the PTS system. Conduct requirements reviews, functional and design reviews, PTS interface development, and Interface Control
Document (ICD) coordination, and integration with Protected Tactical Waveform (PTW) modems (i.e. Air Force-Army Anti-Jam
Modem and Navy Wideband Anti-Jam Modem System).

FY 2025 Plans:
Continue integration, testing, and demonstrations at contractor facilities of two PGET prototypes with PTW modems ECUs,
and payload components to reduce system level risk for each PTS-P space vehicle. Complete relocation and installation of
PGET antennas and digital core from contractor facilities to test site locations. Conduct quick-reaction troubleshooting/deficiency
resolution for PGET during installation, integration, and pre-launch activities at test sites. Conduct planning and OCONUS site
