Title: PTS-Resilient                                                                                                                      0.000     182.787       273.836
Description: The PTS Engineering and Manufacturing Development (EMD) Phase major thrust name has changed to 'PTS-
Resilient', since the milestone decision authority directed the program to transition acquisition pathways from MTA to major
capability acquisition (MCA) within the Technology, Maturation and Risk Reduction (TMRR) phase. This major thrust includes the
development, build, test, and evaluation of the PTS-R space vehicles and payloads to support hosted or free-flyer configurations
available for launch in FY 2031. Includes payload and bus control development/upgrades at the operational centers. Includes
design, development, test, and integration efforts for the PTS-R Ground Entry Terminal (PGET) segment. Deliver Initial
Operational Capability (IOC) for protected communications against threats in FY 2031 with an operational payload. Continue to
mature PTS concept of operations with user participation.

FY 2025 Plans:
Award the PTS-R contract for TMRR phase activities of two PTS-R satellites, gateway terminals, and a ground control segment
for payload and bus control operations. Conduct an Integrated Baseline Review (IBR) and prepare for System Requirements
Review (SRR). Begin systems engineering decomposition activities including requirements analysis and architecture design
for key segments such as space vehicle bus, payload, processor firmware, system controller software, and ground segments.
Purchase initial PTS-R hardware and software systems.
FY 2026 Plans:
Continue and complete TMRR activities for key segments such as space vehicle bus, payload, processor firmware, systems
controller software, and ground segments. Conduct major milestones to include SRR, Preliminary Design Review (PDR), and
Milestone-B. Initiate EMD phase to develop, build, test, and evaluate space vehicles buses, on-board processors, system flight
controller software, and ground segment software to verify that all operational and implied requirements have been met. Prepare
for Critical Design Review (CDR). Continue to purchase PTS-R hardware and software systems.
Rapidly respond to implement system resiliency and situational awareness necessary to operate in the contested space domain.
Activities may include, but are not limited to program office support, studies, technical analysis, experimentation, risk reduction,
prototyping, and activities that may leverage commercial, U.S. Government partnership, and international opportunities to respond
to existing and emerging adversarial threats with speed and agility.
