Title: Protected Tactical Testbed                                                                                                     18.269      17.830         9.351
Description: The Protected Tactical Waveform Testbed is the government's gold standard reference for Protected Tactical
Waveform (PTW) and Key Management System (KMS) within the Protected Tactical SATCOM (PTS) family of systems. Deployed
across government, industry, and FFRDC facilities, it supports PTW development across space, ground, and user terminal
modem segments, including PTS Prototype and Resilient Programs. It enables early interoperability checks and reduces
integration risks among all segments developed by other DoD Services and Agencies. The PTW Testbed also supports on-orbit
testing, system demonstrations, and operational maturation.

FY 2025 Plans:
Continue to demonstrate interoperability between PTS and Mission Management System (MMS) simulator, interoperability/
interface and control of the ECU to the PTS payload, and compatibility with tactical SATCOM family of systems user terminals.
Continue PTW Lead Service duties to demonstrate that PTW will support the department's Core Waveform program, to include
verification of the PTW modem interoperability with the joint force, and validate PTW's role as a core tactical waveform, while
leveraging the PTW Testbed for outreach to coalition and emerging partners, demonstrating interoperability with their existing
space, ground, and terminal assets. Joint SATCOM Engineering Center (JSEC) executes and enables critical testing activities for
PTS contractors. Ensures the development process and impending PTW products adhere to the tenets defined by the established
Service requirements. Develop and integrate the PTW Testbed with ground and user terminal modem segments to advance multi-
Service integration, testing, and fielding of PTW over Wideband Global SATCOM (WGS) capability and user terminal modems,
ensuring early integration with PTS-Prototype program. Deploy and maintain PTW Testbed instances to industry to support
development, integration, and testing of the PTS-Prototype system in preparation for launch. Support PTS-Resilient program's
TMRR technical design reviews and distribute PTW Testbed software and hardware to industry.
FY 2026 Plans:
Continue developing, enhancing, and integrating the PTW Testbed with ground and user terminal modem segments to support
multi-Service testing, fielding, and early operations of PTS users, ensuring synchronization among all segments. Deploy, support,
and maintain PTW Testbed instances across industry, government, and FFRDC facilities to aid in the development, integration,
and ground testing of the PTS-Prototype system in preparation for launch. Integrate PTW Testbed elements with other segments
to support on-orbit demonstrations, testing, and the maturation of the PTS-Prototype. Support PTS-Resilient EMD technical
design reviews and planned progress demonstrations to reduce integration risks. Distribute Testbed software and hardware
updates to industry and government users to support development and integration of PTW-enabled user terminal modems for
commercial constellations in both GEO and MEO orbits, aligning with Force Design objectives. Continue advancing PTW and the
PTW Testbed through ongoing development, testing, and exploration of new capabilities and features to keep pace with threat.
Fulfill PTW Lead Service duties to ensure PTW supports the DoD tactical needs, including verifying PTW modem interoperability

