D. Acquisition Strategy
In December 2017, Principal Deputy Office of the Assistant Secretary of the Air Force Acquisition & Logistics began the GPS IIIF program. Beginning in FY 2019
and, consistent with the Fiscal Year 2016 National Defense Authorization Act, the program was categorized as an Acquisition Category 1B Major Defense Acquisition
Program (MDAP) with the Service Acquisition Executive serving as the Milestone Decision Authority (MDA). During this time, the MDA approved the second phase of
the two-phased GPS III Follow-On (GPS IIIF) acquisition strategy. Executed using funds in PE 1203265F, GPS III Space Segment, the Phase 1 Production Readiness
Feasibility Assessments conducted during FY 2016-2017 provided data and insight into contractors' GPS satellite production designs with emphasis on a mature


