D. Acquisition Strategy
Originally this effort utilized existing DoD engineering/study contracts and activities to conduct science and technology development and data analysis. Preliminary
Government critical design effort for the technology maturation and prototype commenced in FY 2017. A Broad Agency Announcement (BAA) was used to award
seven Integrated System Engineering Team (ISET) contracts which allowed for organizations to participate, advise the government, and gain insight into the prototype
design and build. In May of 2019, DARC was designated as a Middle Tier Acquisition (MTA) program under Section 804 of the 2016 National Defense Authorization Act
(NDAA). In 2020, DARC was directed to proceed with a Rapid Prototyping MTA program for Site 1. The Prime System Integrator (PSI) contract was awarded to Northrop
Grumman Inc. (NG) via a single, competitive award through the Space Enterprise Consortium (SpEC) Other Transaction Authority (OTA)
agreement. The DARC Site 1 MTA rapid prototype program successfully transitioned to a Major Capability Acquisition program that now includes all three DARC sites
under a single program. DARC Site 1 will remain under the awarded OTA contract and DARC Sites 2 & 3 will be awarded under a sole source contract to NG.




