B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                    FY 2024     FY 2025      FY 2026
Title: Space-Based Space Domain Awareness (SDA)                                                                                          111.664     170.100        0.000
Description: SDA includes effective identification, characterization, and understanding of any factor, passive or active, associated
with the space domain.

Performs space-based SDA analysis, research, and development for the SILENTBARKER system in partnership with the NRO.

FY 2025 Plans:
FY 2025 will continue advancing key space-based SDA initiatives to enhance operational capability, resiliency, and strategic
awareness in the contested space domain.

Key planned efforts include:
SILENTBARKER Expansion: Continue development toward Full Operational Capability (FOC) for Geosynchronous (GEO)-based
SDA. This includes mission data processing, dissemination, and prototyping efforts supporting SILENTBARKER and other SDA
initiatives. Technology Enhancements and Prototyping: Advance SDA capabilities through studies, analyses, demonstrations, and
experimentation. Focus areas include threat-responsive upgrades, system extensions, and augmentations for enhanced space-
based surveillance and reconnaissance. Oculus Hosted Payload Program: Continue preparations for the launch of the first Oculus
SDA Hosted Payload (HP) on a commercial platform. FY 2025 will also support initial integration and characterization efforts of
the second prototype payload. The Oculus initiative provides a cost-effective gap-filler for GEO-based SDA, expanding capability
through commercial, international, or government hosting solutions. Prototype Missions: Support launch, on-orbit experimentation,
and operations of key AFRL and SSC partnership programs, including Oracle-Mobility (Oracle-M) and Super-synchronous
Small Satellite Space Surveillance System (S6) satellites, which enable critical low-cost space-based experimentation and
expand SDA operations into Cislunar and GEO space. Enterprise Support and Resiliency: Enable the integration, testing, and
operationalization of SDA systems with a focus on resiliency and situational awareness. Activities may include Command and
Control (C2) systems support, technical analysis, integration events, space test/combat range exercises, and mission partner
interfaces. Collaboration and Partnerships: Leverage commercial, interagency, and international opportunities to rapidly respond
to emerging threats and expand SDA capabilities through innovation and collaboration.
FY 2026 Plans:
Mandatory (reconciliation) funding in FY2026 will continue advancing space-based SDA capabilities critical to operations in the
contested space domain, with a focus on system resiliency, prototyping, and operational experimentation.

