Note
This program, BA 5, PE 1206771SF, project 650008, CASR, is a new start.

A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
CASR is a contractually managed framework that ensures DoD has access to commercial space capabilities throughout the spectrum of conflict. CASR ensures
that commercial capabilities, integrated during peacetime, can be leveraged throughout the spectrum of conflict and that they remain secure, reliable, and available
to support the warfighter. This funding supports CASR baseline operating costs as well as threat sharing; wargaming/exercises; a CASR readiness and inspection
program; and additional incentive structures. Near-term funding (FY 2026) supports participation of approximately 10 CASR companies.

Specific surge capacity within CASR may include: Leveraging commercial capabilities already on orbit; augmenting existing USSF missions with added capacity (e.g.,
SATCOM); reach back into existing production lines to rapidly acquire satellites, payloads, and launch vehicles; denial of service over a region or to a certain customer
set; and other potential concepts.

Rapidly delivers impactful commercial solutions to the warfighter by identifying viable capabilities, implementing development contracts, and integrating them into the
USSF ecosystem

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                    FY 2024         FY 2025        FY 2026
Title: CASR                                                                                                                                   -               -          23.671
Description: CASR provides a foundational capability across all mission areas to ensure commercial capabilities are fully
integrated into operations and available immediately during a crisis or conflict to combatant commands. It provides threat sharing,
wargame/exercise participation; contract readiness and incentives, etc., to CASR companies to fully integrate and assure
commercial capabilities are available across the spectrum of conflict at CCMD's timing/tempo to achieve operational objectives.
CASR ensures commercial solutions for joint requirements/capabilities are met during crisis or conflict. CASR predetermines
commercial capability and actions during crisis, with known cost points, and enables training/exercising/wargaming with these
"surge" capabilities during peacetime, assuring understood and integrated effects.




