This strategic initiative also bolsters operational effectiveness in contested environments by integrating alternative technologies,
fostering commercial innovation, and enhancing resilience and awareness across critical domains.

FY 2026 Plans:
Fund operating baseline as well as threat sharing for initial COMSATCOM, SDA and key commercial contracts; wargaming/
exercise participation for approximately 10 commercial participants; CASR readiness and inspection program; and incentives.
Rapidly respond to implement system resiliency and situational awareness necessary to operate in the contested space domain.

Leverages commercial capabilities to include integrating alternate PNT constellations enabling a more resilient PNT architecture
to complement GPS, demonstrating space superiority operations with on-orbit assets, combining payloads for multi-domain
aware-ness on tactical space assets, and advancing commercial multi-domain awareness and cyber capabilities.

Activities may include, but are not limited to program office support, studies, technical analysis, experimentation, risk reduction,
prototyping, and activities that may leverage commercial, U.S. Government partnership, and international opportunities to respond
to existing and emerging adversarial threats with speed and agility.
FY 2025 to FY 2026 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Funds 7.750M in operating costs for CASR baseline program and CASR objectives. This funding continues FY25 Congressional
Add initiatives; CASR is not a new start.

Also, 15.921M million was erroneously programmed into Project 650008, Commercial Augmentation Space Reserve. During
the year of execution, the 15.921M will be internally realigned to the Commercial Capability Integration project within the same
PE to support the integration of alternate PNT constellations enabling a more resilient PNT architecture to complement GPS,
integration and demonstration of space superiority operations with on-orbit assets, integration and launch of payloads for multi-
domain awareness on tactical space assets, and advancing commercial multi-domain awareness and cyber capabilities to support
multiple mission areas.
