B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                       FY 2024         FY 2025     FY 2026
Title: NSTTC                                                                                                                                 21.827         196.702     141.835
Description: Supports the development of the NSTTC to deliver physical and digital environments, systems, tools and capabilities
critical for developmental and operational test, training, exercises, wargames, and tactics development for space systems. Include
development, demonstration, and continuous delivery test and training, hardware and software that yield the capabilities required
to test, validate, and verify performance of integrated space systems and Guardians that operate and train them. Provides a safe,
secure, and realistic, relevant space-based physical and digital arena for controlled space, ground, and cyber systems to support
test and training needs.

Cyber Range: Provides live and simulated cyber operations and security test and training. Delivers USSF systems Verification,
Validation, and Accreditation (VV&A) to ensure cyber resiliency, security, and interoperability.

Electromagnetic Spectrum Operations Range: Provides ground-based system, range control, and on-orbit surrogate for
Electronic Warfare (EW), Satellite Communications (SATCOM), and Position Navigation and Timing (PNT) test and training.

Orbital Range: Provides sensor and data fusion to enable live, on-orbit Orbital Warfare (OW) test and training. On-orbit range
system supports execution of exquisite, discrete demonstrations.

Digital Test & Training: In concert with Program Element 1203174SF, Project 674671 (Enterprise Training Services Development
Project), delivers digital environments, connectivity, and cradle-to-grave Modeling and Simulation (M&S) to enable operational
test, operator training and tactics development in USSF and Joint exercises, and wargaming. Consists of framework, applications,
physical hardware, simulation, and data management needed to support operational test and training needs.

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                      FY 2024     FY 2025      FY 2026
Infrastructure: Delivers the computer, storage, data management, and connectivity backbone, at all classification levels, to enable
an integrated NSTTC framework across Space Force, Joint, and Government owned environments. Consists of facilities support,
common network infrastructure, cloud hosting, data centers, platform services and the cybersecurity required to analyze and
share data as well as integrate and distribute test and training systems. Provides access to the test and training users, range
operators, range developers, integrating programs and partners systems.

Readiness: Delivers and utilizes virtual environments, connectivity, tools, and applications for USSF and Joint Exercises and
Wargames to enable Guardian advanced training and readiness to be presented to the Combatant Commands. Provides materiel
solutions to rapidly address short-term Guardian training and tactics capability gaps.

FY 2025 Plans:
- Continue investments in Cyber, Electromagnetic, and Orbital ranges, including foundational infrastructure development as well
as modernization and improvement of existing capabilities to keep current with military priorities, evolving threats, and advanced
training involving USSF and joint systems and operations
- Continue development of Electromagnetic Spectrum range C3, terminal, data generation systems
- Continue support to warfighting community of EW advanced training environment
- Continue development of integrated data transport architecture across the ranges
- Continue developing digital High-End Advanced Test, Training, and Tactics Development (HEAT3) platform to enable enduring
Joint Simulation Environment (JSE)-based digital test and training architecture
- Begin development of digital range operations capabilities via Commercial Solutions Openings (CSOs)
FY 2026 Plans:
- Continue investments in Cyber, Electromagnetic, and Orbital ranges, including foundational infrastructure development as well
as modernization and improvement of existing capabilities to keep current with military priorities, evolving threats, and advanced
training involving USSF and joint systems and operations
- Continue development of Electromagnetic Spectrum range C3, terminal, data generation systems
- Continue support to warfighting community of EW advanced training environment
- Continue development of integrated data transport architecture across the ranges
- Continue developing digital High-End Advanced Test, Training, and Tactics Development (HEAT3) platform to enable enduring
Joint Simulation Environment (JSE)-based digital test and training architecture
- Deliver Minimum Viable Product (MVP)-level digital HEAT3 platform for initial JSE integration; deliver and integrate initial set of
intel-validated threat models, enabling HEAT3 platform to support test and training relevant to top-priority DoD threat scenario
- Continue development of advanced and combat training capabilities for exercises and wargames. Deliver MVP medium fidelity
digital capability to support evolved Space Flag requirements.

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                             FY 2024    FY 2025      FY 2026
- Continue development of digital range operations via CSOs
FY 2025 to FY 2026 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY 2026 decrease of -54.867M based on planned development and fielding activities in the program baselines within the Maj T&E
portfolio, as well as efficiencies in alignment with Executive Order 14222.
