Readiness: Delivers and utilizes virtual environments, connectivity, tools, and applications for USSF and Joint Exercises and
Wargames to enable Guardian advanced training and readiness to be presented to the Combatant Commands. Provides materiel
solutions to rapidly address short-term Guardian training and tactics capability gaps.

FY 2025 Plans:
- Continue investments in Cyber, Electromagnetic, and Orbital ranges, including foundational infrastructure development as well
as modernization and improvement of existing capabilities to keep current with military priorities, evolving threats, and advanced
training involving USSF and joint systems and operations
- Continue development of Electromagnetic Spectrum range C3, terminal, data generation systems
- Continue support to warfighting community of EW advanced training environment
- Continue development of integrated data transport architecture across the ranges
- Continue developing digital High-End Advanced Test, Training, and Tactics Development (HEAT3) platform to enable enduring
Joint Simulation Environment (JSE)-based digital test and training architecture
- Begin development of digital range operations capabilities via Commercial Solutions Openings (CSOs)
FY 2026 Plans:
- Continue investments in Cyber, Electromagnetic, and Orbital ranges, including foundational infrastructure development as well
as modernization and improvement of existing capabilities to keep current with military priorities, evolving threats, and advanced
training involving USSF and joint systems and operations
- Continue development of Electromagnetic Spectrum range C3, terminal, data generation systems
- Continue support to warfighting community of EW advanced training environment
- Continue development of integrated data transport architecture across the ranges
- Continue developing digital High-End Advanced Test, Training, and Tactics Development (HEAT3) platform to enable enduring
Joint Simulation Environment (JSE)-based digital test and training architecture
- Deliver Minimum Viable Product (MVP)-level digital HEAT3 platform for initial JSE integration; deliver and integrate initial set of
intel-validated threat models, enabling HEAT3 platform to support test and training relevant to top-priority DoD threat scenario
- Continue development of advanced and combat training capabilities for exercises and wargames. Deliver MVP medium fidelity
digital capability to support evolved Space Flag requirements.


